<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-11-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-11-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="220" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d220">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/3.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé
                                    d’Affaires</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Santo
                                        Domingo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-11-20"><hi rend="italic">November 20,
                                    1911</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>President Cáceres shot fatally this afternoon.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Endicott.</hi></signed></closer>
